set_visible_bumps(25.10)                              set_visible_bumps(25.10)

Name
       set_visible_bumps  -  Displays  only  the bumps with the specified bump
       cell names and hides all other bumps

Syntax
       set_visible_bumps

       [-help]

       {-bump_cells <bump_cell_name>| -all}

       Displays only the bumps with the specified bump cell  names  and  hides
       all other bumps.

       To redisplay all bumps, specify the -all parameter.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each set_visible_bumps parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_visible_bumps

       -all   Displays all bumps.

              By  default, all bumps are displayed. When you specify set_visi-
              ble_bumps <bump_cell_name>, the tool  displays  only  the  bumps
              with  the  specified  bump cell names and hides all other bumps.
              You can then  use  set_visible_bumps  <-all>  to  redisplay  all
              bumps.

       -bump_cells <names>
              Displays  only  the bumps with the specified bump cell names and
              hides all other bumps. You can specify multiple bump cell names.

Examples
              * The following command displays only the bumps with  bump  cell
                as BUMPCELL:

                set_visible_bumps -bump_cells BUMPCELL

              * The following command redisplays all bumps:

                set_visible_bumps -all

